- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses a tile assembly model and the ability to replicate shapes, which could be considered a data structure or algorithmic problem. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper discusses the abilities of self-assembling tiles, which could be analyzed in terms of computational complexity. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics): The paper involves the study of discrete objects (tiles) and their ability to self-assemble, which could be considered a topic in discrete mathematics. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry): The paper involves the replication of 2-dimensional shapes, which could be considered a topic in computational geometry.
